ADP, Gilead, MetLife, Ness Technologies: U.S. Equity Preview

-- B y   N i k o l a j   G a m m e l t o f t   a n d   I n y o u n g   H w a n g
-- 
2011-06-10T22:25:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/adp-gilead-metlife-ness-technologies-u-s-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in U.S. trading on June 13. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of 6:20 p.m. in New York.  Automatic Data Processing Inc. (ADP)  : The paycheck
processing company said it will buy back up to an additional 35
million shares.  Gilead Sciences Inc. (GILD)   slumped 2 percent to $39.43.
The world’s biggest seller of AIDS medicines said the U.S.
Justice Department is investigating the company’s drug
production and distribution. Cara Miller, a Gilead spokeswoman,
declined to comment beyond the company’s statement and
regulatory filing.  MetLife Inc. (MET)  : The biggest U.S. life insurer said
storms in April and May cost as much as 6.7 times the company’s
provision for such expenses at the home and auto business.  Ness Technologies Inc. (NSTC US) jumped 11 percent to
$7.43. The computer-services provider said it agreed to be
acquired by an affiliate of Citi Venture Capital International
in a cash transaction valued at about $307 million.  To contact the reporters on this story:
